name: Scarab Amulet Bag
description: This small purse is beaded by hand in Brick Stitch using size 11* Japanese Seed Beads. Over 3500 beads were added one at a time, the thread passing through each bead 2-3 times making this lovely accessory sturdy heirloom quality. Rich colors Ruby Red, Amythest, Sky Blue, Cobalt, Green and Metallic Gold. Strap is made from Seed Beads and Bugle beads measuring 28" in length. The purse body is approximately 4"x3 1/2". The fringe is 3 1/2" at its longest point finished with a Crystal Blue Faceted Teardrop. Fastens with handmade toggle clasp of Seed Beads and 4mm Ice Blue Swarovski Crystal Bicone Beads. Scarab Pattern designed by Esoteric Beads and can be purchased at www.Etsy.com/shop/EsotericBeads

name: Carnelian Celtic Cone Earrings
description:
Cracked Carnelian 10mm and 3mm Round Gemstone Beads, Brass cone bead. Detailed Celtic design cone. Hook wires for pierced ears. 
The most favorable pieces are a deep red to red-orange hue. Carnelian has a long and storied past, and was once considered strictly the property of the noble class. People holding a high social status were often buried with this gem stone.
